    <item>
      <title>GitHub</title>
      <link>https://dhamejanishivam.github.io/blogs/posts/second_blog/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 21 Aug 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://dhamejanishivam.github.io/blogs/posts/second_blog/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h4 id=&#34;github-is-a-platform-that-allows-software-developers-to-store-share-and-manage-their-code-it-also-enables-collaboration-with-other-developers&#34;&gt;GitHub is a platform that allows software developers to store, share, and manage their code. It also enables collaboration with other developers.&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt; 
 &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;some-features-of-github&#34;&gt;Some features of GitHub:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You can upload your code and store it securely.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You can host static websites directly from your repositories.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You can share your code with other developers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Other developers can contribute to your repositories (if you allow it), and you can do the same for theirs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;(These are just some of the features. GitHub is constantly adding more.)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
